author: Michael C. Bender
title: U.S. Cuts Aid to Cambodia in Wake of Disputed Election
text:
WASHINGTON—The U.S. announced it will cut off $8.3 million in financial aid for Cambodia after “recent setbacks to democracy” in the country, including a round of Senate elections on Sunday in which the ruling party claimed victory in all 58 races.
Financial support will be curtailed for the Cambodian military, the nation’s tax department and certain local governments, White House press secretary Sarah Sanders said Tuesday.
